+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017UzhiRZPqHeZRrZEi1Mn1M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HpS4NyKdELJ9oREDsEXvUy","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-collab-editor-design.md","content":"# Collaborative Real-Time Document Editor - Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n4 source modules in `src/`:\n- `db.ts` — SQLite database layer (CRUD, versions)\n- `ot.ts` — Operational Transformation engine\n- `routes.ts` — Express REST routes\n- `server.ts` — Entry point, createApp factory, WebSocket handling\n\n## OT Model\n\nTwo operation types:\n- `insert(position, text)` — inserts text at position\n- `delete(position, count)` — deletes count chars at position\n\nServer maintains canonical document state + version number. Clients send ops with `baseVersion`. Server transforms incoming ops against all ops applied since `baseVersion`, applies the result, increments version, broadcasts to other clients.\n\nTransform function: Given two concurrent ops A and B, produce A' and B' such that applying A then B' yields the same result as applying B then A'.\n\n## WebSocket Protocol\n\nPath: `/ws/documents/:id`\n\nMessages (JSON):\n- Server→Client `sync`: `{type: \"sync\", content, version}`\n- Client→Server `operation`: `{type: \"operation\", op: {type, position, text/count}, baseVersion}`\n- Server→Client `operation`: `{type: \"operation\", op, version, clientId}`\n- Server→Client `ack`: `{type: \"ack\", version}`\n- Server→Client `error`: `{type: \"error\", message}`\n\n## REST API\n\n- `POST /documents` — create (body: {title, content?})\n- `GET /documents` — list all\n- `GET /documents/:id` — get one\n- `PUT /documents/:id` — update (body: {title?, content?})\n- `DELETE /documents/:id` — delete\n- `GET /documents/:id/versions` — version history\n\n## Persistence\n\nSQLite with existing schema.sql tables. Each applied operation creates a version record. Document content column always reflects latest state.\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. Client connects to WS, receives sync with current content + version\n2. Client sends operation with baseVersion\n3. Server loads ops since baseVersion from version history\n4. Server transforms incoming op against those ops\n5. Server applies transformed op to document content\n6. Server saves new version, broadcasts to other clients\n7. Server sends ack to originating client\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":537,"cache_read_input_tokens":25181,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":537},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee43e690-08e9-4cbd-87ba-bf103b9279c3","uuid":"048cc9c2-ae07-4dc9-bfce-3ee152da3b21"}
