+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AfRR4bPX37GoFVgNgZvm83","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a summary of everything that was done:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Deleted\n- `/workspace/src/ws.test.ts` -- the old monolithic WebSocket test file with all tests in a single `test()` block.\n\n### Created (5 new test files)\n\n1. **`/workspace/src/ws-sync.test.ts`** (2 tests)\n   - `sync on connect` -- creates a doc, connects via WS, verifies the sync message has `type`, `content`, `version`, and `clientId`\n   - `reject non-existent doc` -- connects to a nonexistent doc ID and verifies the close event fires\n\n2. **`/workspace/src/ws-ops.test.ts`** (2 tests)\n   - `insert operation` -- creates doc \"Hello\", inserts \" World\" at position 5 with baseVersion 1, checks ack version=2, verifies content via HTTP\n   - `delete operation` -- creates doc \"Hello World\", deletes at position 5 count 6, verifies \"Hello\"\n\n3. **`/workspace/src/ws-broadcast.test.ts`** (1 test)\n   - `broadcast to other clients` -- creates doc \"AB\", connects 2 clients, sends insert \"C\" at pos 2 from ws1, verifies ws1 gets ack and ws2 gets broadcast operation\n\n4. **`/workspace/src/ws-errors.test.ts`** (1 test)\n   - `error handling` -- sequentially tests bad JSON, missing baseVersion, unknown type, and negative position. Each sub-test creates a new doc and connection, gets sync, sends bad message, checks error response, then closes WS\n\n5. **`/workspace/src/ws-ot.test.ts`** (2 tests)\n   - `OT convergence with concurrent edits` (10s timeout) -- creates \"abc\", connects 2 clients, ws1 inserts \"X\" at 1 (v1), ws2 gets broadcast then inserts \"Y\" at 2 (v1), verifies content has both X and Y and length 5\n   - `10 concurrent clients` (30s timeout) -- connects 10 clients, each inserts sequentially with proper version tracking, draining broadcasts between ops, verifies all 10 characters present\n\n### Key Implementation Detail\n\nEach test file contains the four helper functions (`httpReq`, `openWs`, `nextMsg`, `closeWs`). The helpers use a message queue pattern (via a module-level `Map<WebSocket, Record<string, unknown>[]>`) because in this environment, the server's sync message can arrive before `nextMsg` registers its listener. The `openWs` function registers a persistent `message` listener that pushes to a queue, and `nextMsg` reads from that queue (with polling fallback for messages that arrive after the call).\n\nEach test creates its own server instance via `createApp()` and calls `s.stop()` at the end, ensuring full isolation between tests."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2af8da (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61769\ntool_uses: 39\nduration_ms: 325971</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee43e690-08e9-4cbd-87ba-bf103b9279c3","uuid":"874d6874-d061-4c85-90e1-1c8357858d8c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to split WebSocket tests into multiple small test files (1-2 tests each) because vitest has issues with many WS connections in a single test file in this environment. Each file should contain the httpReq, openWs, nextMsg, and closeWs helper functions, and each test should create its own server with createApp() and close it at the end.\n\nWrite the following test files in /workspace/src/:\n\n1. ws-sync.test.ts - Test sync on connect + reject non-existent doc\n2. ws-ops.test.ts - Test insert operation + delete operation \n3. ws-broadcast.test.ts - Test broadcast to other clients\n4. ws-errors.test.ts - Test error handling (bad json, missing baseVersion, unknown type, negative position) \n5. ws-ot.test.ts - Test OT convergence with concurrent edits + 10 concurrent clients\n\nEach file should:\n- Import from './server.js', 'ws', 'http', 'vitest'\n- Have helper functions: httpReq(port, method, path, body?), openWs(port, docId), nextMsg(ws), closeWs(ws)\n- Each test creates its own server via createApp(), starts it, runs the test, and calls s.stop()\n- Use proper await closeWs() between sequential WS usages\n- Have 10000ms timeout per test, 30000ms for the 10 concurrent clients test\n\nThe helpers should be:\n```typescript\nfunction httpReq(port: number, method: string, path: string, body?: unknown): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const data = body ? JSON.stringify(body) : undefined;\n    const headers: Record<string, string> = {};\n    if (data) { headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json'; headers['Content-Length'] = String(Buffer.byteLength(data)); }\n    const req = http.request({ hostname: 'localhost', port, path, method, headers }, (res) => {\n      let raw = '';\n      res.on('data', (d: Buffer) => raw += d);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(raw ? JSON.parse(raw) : {}); } catch { resolve({}); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', reject);\n    if (data) req.write(data);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction openWs(port: number, docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/documents/${docId}`);\n    ws.on('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.on('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction nextMsg(ws: WebSocket): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const t = setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('msg timeout')), 5000);\n    ws.once('message', (d) => { clearTimeout(t); resolve(JSON.parse(d.toString())); });\n  });\n}\n\nfunction closeWs(ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    if (ws.readyState === WebSocket.CLOSED) { resolve(); return; }\n    ws.on('close', () => resolve());\n    ws.close();\n  });\n}\n```\n\nAlso DELETE the old /workspace/src/ws.test.ts file.\n\nFor the ws-sync test: first test creates doc, connects WS, checks sync message has type/content/version/clientId, then closeWs. Second test connects to nonexistent doc and verifies close event fires.\n\nFor ws-ops: first test creates doc \"Hello\", inserts \" World\" at position 5 with baseVersion 1, checks ack version=2, verifies content via HTTP. Second test creates \"Hello World\", deletes at position 5 count 6, verifies \"Hello\".\n\nFor ws-broadcast: creates doc \"AB\", connects 2 clients, sends insert \"C\" at pos 2 from ws1, verifies ws1 gets ack and ws2 gets broadcast operation.\n\nFor ws-errors: single test that sequentially tests bad json, missing baseVersion, unknown type, negative position. Each sub-test creates a new doc and connection, gets sync, sends bad message, checks error response, then closeWs.\n\nFor ws-ot: first test creates \"abc\", connects 2 clients, ws1 inserts \"X\" at 1 (v1), ws2 gets broadcast then inserts \"Y\" at 2 (v1), verify content has both X and Y and length 5. Second test connects 10 clients, each inserts sequentially with proper version tracking, draining broadcasts between ops, verifies all 10 characters present.","agentId":"a2af8da","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a summary of everything that was done:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Deleted\n- `/workspace/src/ws.test.ts` -- the old monolithic WebSocket test file with all tests in a single `test()` block.\n\n### Created (5 new test files)\n\n1. **`/workspace/src/ws-sync.test.ts`** (2 tests)\n   - `sync on connect` -- creates a doc, connects via WS, verifies the sync message has `type`, `content`, `version`, and `clientId`\n   - `reject non-existent doc` -- connects to a nonexistent doc ID and verifies the close event fires\n\n2. **`/workspace/src/ws-ops.test.ts`** (2 tests)\n   - `insert operation` -- creates doc \"Hello\", inserts \" World\" at position 5 with baseVersion 1, checks ack version=2, verifies content via HTTP\n   - `delete operation` -- creates doc \"Hello World\", deletes at position 5 count 6, verifies \"Hello\"\n\n3. **`/workspace/src/ws-broadcast.test.ts`** (1 test)\n   - `broadcast to other clients` -- creates doc \"AB\", connects 2