+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the entire conversation:\n\n1. **Initial Task**: The user provided a task to build a collaborative real-time document editing server (T2) with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, OT-based conflict resolution, SQLite persistence, and robustness for 10+ concurrent clients.\n\n2. **Skill Invocation**: The brainstorming skill was invoked, followed by the TDD skill. Non-interactive/autopilot mode was used.\n\n3. **Design Decisions**: \n   - OT (Operational Transformation) for conflict resolution\n   - Linear operations (insert/delete at position)\n   - JSON messages with type field for WebSocket protocol\n   - Path-based WebSocket: `/ws/documents/:id`\n   - Monotonically increasing version per document\n   - 4 modules: db.ts, ot.ts, routes.ts, server.ts\n   - Standard REST API design\n\n4. **Implementation Order (TDD)**:\n   - OT engine (ot.ts) - 20 tests, all passed\n   - Database layer (db.ts) - 13 tests, all passed\n   - REST routes (routes.ts) - 12 tests, all passed\n   - Server with WebSocket (server.ts) - had significant issues with vitest and WebSocket tests\n\n5. **Major Issue**: WebSocket tests kept timing out in vitest. The root cause was that vitest's worker threads don't properly handle multiple WebSocket connections across multiple test functions in a single file. The fix was to split WebSocket tests into multiple small files (1-2 tests each), each creating their own server instance.\n\n6. **Errors encountered**:\n   - `import.meta.dirname` was undefined → fixed by using `fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)` with fallback inline schema\n   - WebSocket tests timing out → discovered it was a vitest issue with multiple WS connections per test file → split into multiple test files\n   - supertest with