tions\n   - Server-authoritative OT: server transforms incoming ops against concurrent ops since client's baseVersion\n   - WebSocket upgrade handling via `noServer` mode with path-based routing `/ws/documents/:id`\n   - SQLite with WAL journal mode and foreign keys\n   - Version tracking per document (monotonically increasing)\n   - Express REST API with JSON body parsing\n   - Vitest for testing with per-test server lifecycle pattern for WebSocket tests\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - `/workspace/src/ot.ts` - OT engine with `apply()` and `transform()` functions\n     - Core algorithm: two operation types (`InsertOp`, `DeleteOp`), transform functions for all pairs (insert-insert, insert-delete, delete-delete)\n     - Tiebreak: at same position, operation A wins (goes first)\n     - Convergence property: `apply(apply(doc, A), B') == apply(apply(doc, B), A')`\n     ```typescript\n     export interface InsertOp { type: 'insert'; position: number; text: string; }\n     export interface DeleteOp { type: 'delete'; position: number; count: number; }\n     export type Operation = InsertOp | DeleteOp;\n     export function apply(doc: string, op: Operation): string { ... }\n     export function transform(a: Operation, b: Operation): [Operation, Operation] { ... }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/src/db.ts` - Database layer wrapping better-sqlite3\n     - Uses `fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)` to locate schema.sql, with inline fallback\n     - Prepared statements for all operations\n     - Creates initial version (v1) on document creation\n     - `addVersion()` also updates document content\n     ```typescript\n     export interface Db {\n       createDocument(title: string, content?: string): Document;\n       getDocument(id: string): Document | undefined;\n       listDocuments(): Document[];\n       updateDocument(id: string, updates: { title?: string; content?: string }): Document | undefined;\n       deleteDocument(id: string): boolean;\n       addVersion(docId: string, version: number, content: string, operation: Operation): void;\n       getVersions(docId: string): Version[];\n       getOperationsSince(docId: string, sinceVersion: number): VersionWithOp[];\n       getCurrentVersion(docId: string): number;\n       updateDocumentContent(docId: string, content: string): void;\n       close(): void;\n     }\n     export function createDb(dbPath?: string): Db { ... }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/src/routes.ts` - Express REST routes\n     - `POST /documents` (201), `GET /documents`, `GET /documents/:id`, `PUT /documents/:id`, `DELETE /documents/:id` (204), `GET /documents/:id/versions`\n     - Validates title is required on POST, returns 404 for non-existent docs\n     ```typescript\n     export function createRouter(db: Db): Router { ... }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/src/server.ts` - Main entry point with createApp factory\n     - Creates Express app + http.Server + WebSocketServer (noServer mode)\n     - Handles upgrade requests matching `/ws/documents/:id`\n     - Room-based connection tracking (Map<documentId, Set<ClientConnection>>)\n     - On WS connect: sends sync message with current content + version + clientId\n     - On operation message: transforms against concurrent ops, applies, saves version, sends ack, broadcasts\n     - Validates operations (type, position >= 0, etc.)\n     - Returns `{app: httpServer, start(port?), stop(), db}`\n     ```typescript\n     export function createApp(dbPath?: string) {\n       // ... returns { app: httpServer, start, stop, db }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/src/ot.test.ts` - 20 tests for OT engine (apply + transform + convergence)\n   - `/workspace/src/db.test.ts` - 13 tests for database CRUD, versions, persistence\n   - `/workspace/src/routes.test.ts` - 12 tests for REST API using supertest\n   - `/workspace/src/ws-sync.test.ts` - 2 tests: sync on connect, reject non-existent doc\n   - `/workspace/src/ws-ops.test.ts` - 2 tests: insert operation, delete operation\n   - `/workspace/src/ws-broadcast.test.ts` - 1 test: broadcast to other clients\n   - `/workspace/src/ws-errors.test.ts` - 1 test: bad json, missing baseVersion, unknown type, negative position\n   - `/workspace/src/ws-ot.test.ts` - 2 tests: OT convergence with 2 clients, 10 concurrent clients\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-collab-editor-design.md` - Design document\n   - `/workspace/schema.sql` - Pre-existing DB schema (documents, versions, active_connections tables)\n   - `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Existing config (globals: true, testTimeout: 10000)\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **`import.meta.dirname` undefined**: When running via tsx/vitest, `import.meta.dirname` was undefined causing `TypeError: The \"path\" argument must be of type string`. Fixed by using `path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))` instead, with an inline fallback schema if the file can't be found.\n   \n   - **WebSocket tests timing out in vitest**: This was the biggest issue. Tests with multiple WebSocket connections per test file consistently timed out (WS `open` event never fired or `message` never received). After extensive debugging:\n     - Discovered `supertest(server.app)` interfered with WebSocket connections → switched to raw `http.request`\n     - Discovered `beforeAll` shared server + multiple tests → always timed out\n     - Discovered multiple test functions with WS in single file → timed out\n     - Discovered single test with proper `await closeWs()` between connections → worked\n     - **Final fix**: Used a subagent to split WS tests into 5 small files (ws-sync, ws-ops, ws-broadcast, ws-errors, ws-ot), each with 1-2 tests, each creating its own server instance per test. Tests properly await WS close before opening new connections. All helper functions (httpReq, openWs, nextMsg, closeWs) duplicated in each file.\n\n   - **No user feedback/corrections were given** - the user only provided the initial task.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - OT transform algorithm implemented cor